<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karadin>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NB-GM<BR>
And supermodel</span><br>  Posts: 465<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/22/03 11:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Some Curiosities about RTA Rules?</span><hr size=1> Bog,<br>
<br>
<br>
The rule doesn't apply to single mobs, because no one stops mid-KT pull and runs off to whack Yelinak.  It just doesn't happen nor make sense.<br>
<br>
In VT, there really is no good place to stop, run out for rotation mobs, and then come right back to, and a little bit less so, N ToV (there is more than one safe spot for a COH mage, but they are spooky).  In VT,  you could stop after DXXT like you would on any first night of your VT clearing, and in N ToV, you usually would stop at Aary pit, even if you killed Vyemm or Fesh before stopping for the night.  In both cases, you get the protection of your mobs from other guilds running in and killing what you have left up.  Running out to kill other mobs, while holding those mobs &quot;hostage&quot; if you will, is hoarding.<br>
<br>
Another &quot;fear&quot;, especially with VT, is people might jump out to grab Cursed or Emp (the only mobs I can think of on rotation that might possibly be worth leaving VT for), and having a patch or server crash keep them from getting Aten, and then asking for an additional VT spot.  (Currently, if you clear day one, and there is a server down on day two before you get to Aten, you get another turn usually.)  So running out to whack Cursed, and then losing Aten, and insisting on a second full VT run is also quite a bit unfair.  You chose Cursed as being more important, and the server lost an Aten because of that choice.  This rule keeps that from happening.<br>
<br>
The rule didn't start when we passed mobs on our first VT, it started back in the N ToV days with SoT and BotS.  Before this rule, there was a lot of mob jumping when one guild would stop for the night, as people tried to grab whatever was left up.  The result, once SoT was fully on rotation (for a while, N ToV went dragon by dragon), this rule came into being, so that SoT (raided on euro time) and BotS (early EST) wouldn't have to worry about their mobs being taken over &quot;night&quot;.<br>
<br>
Since VT is much the same, the same rule applies.  NB has a mage logged out in several places in VT, so if this rule wasn't in place, we could easily wait till SOTE or FK stopped for the night, and run in and clear Named.  That wouldn't be very gentlemanly, and the rule makes sense.  However, much like the argument with teaming, it isn't very fair to the rest of the rotation guilds to grab a bunch of other mobs midraid while having those other mobs protected.<br>
<br>
It's really easy to deal with actually - if there is a mob up you really want (say Emp or Cursed), and it's before you start your VT run, you go grab them first, then head to VT.  If it's on the last day, finish VT and then go whack them.  If it spawns in the middle, and you take three days to clear VT, you probably won't be able to port out, kill the mob(s) and still clear VT in a timely manner anyway.  So this rule keeps mobs and multi-day rotations moving forward and keeps hoarding to a minimum.<br>
<br>
I completely agree that some guilds are capable of killing 8 mobs a night, and some take all night to kill 1, and both guilds should be protected under the system.  But let's remember one of the basics of the system - the faster mob X dies, the sooner he respawns for the next group.  Hoarding 6 named in VT while clearing 2-3 mobs outside is taking a tad bit advantage of the guild next up on rotation for VT who would gladly go in and clear those 6 Named (especially since one of those would be Aten).  It also risks that while hoarding those 6 VT Named, the server crashes as I pointed out above.  Basically, it comes down to priorities - which is more important, the named in VT or mob X, Y, or Z outside VT.  Make your choice if you won't have enough time to clear both, and pass the others.  If you can finish VT and the other mobs, more power to you.  The simple rule of thumb I use in choosing priorities: always choose your targets as if the server was going to crash imminently (which with SOE is always a possibility).<br>
<br>
So I would have to say that these factors lead me to continue to believe in and support the idea that if you leave a multi-day rotation spot, your rotation turn for those is done.  That way, the server is guaranteed, as much as is possible, that the best loot mobs will get killed as quickly as possible.  What I would say as a caveat, is that if you are able to kill a rotation mob with a small force, while STILL killing in VT or N ToV (think Trak or Statue), then I would have no problem with that.  Both rotations are moving forward, and you have not left VT or N ToV (in essence).  Obviously that applies to very few rotation mobs (i.e. you won't dispatch a Cursed or Emp force and still have numbers for VT).  The important deciding factor (for me) is, are you still actively killing in VT or N ToV? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kenaukamikaze>Kenau Kamikaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>VoF - GL</span><br>  Posts: 354<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/22/03 12:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Some Curiosities about RTA Rules?</span><hr size=1> What Bogarthamule is referring to, is this situation, that indeed actually happened:<br>
We were up for CT, but since we are the only european guild, we will have to book fear ourselves and clear it and then kill CT in the same run. If we do not do this then there is no way we can kill CT, because when any USA guild finishes their turn in Fear, we are already sleeping. So we had fear booked for Monday since the weekends are always booked solid.<br>
Saturay before that our turn on NToV came up so we went in, cleared our way and then killed Eashen, Ikatiar, Aaryonar, Vyemm, Dragarn and Feshlak like we always do and were about to camp for the night, when we received a tell from the guild in Fear that they were done and that we could go in and kill CT.<br>
So a couple of us camped in NToV and went to sleep anyway, others camped and logged in other toons, and some simply ported out and we went and waxed CT. Thereby speeding up the CT rot by 2 days. Because now he died saturday evening, while otherwise he would not have died untill monday evening.<br>
Sunday we logged in again at our normal raidtime, CoH'd up the people who had left ToV to help kill CT and/or exp and we went on and cleared the rest of ToV.<br>
Would the server have crashed that night then we would not have been up for NToV again, because we already had killed Aaryonar and some of his friends, so nothing would have been lost. We would  NOT have been able to finish NToV that day, because we were about to camp already when that tell came.<br>
It just costed us half an hour extra to start the next day to CoH the people that had left. <br>
I do not think we did anything wrong or were *hoarding* mobs. <br>
We have also had it happen that, while we were clearing PoG to get to Tunare, a call for help came to kill Ragefire from a cleric who's guildies were not online yet. I guess  she did a /w all cleric and saw us in PoG. (This was before the spawnable RF obviously, when clerics sat for weeks on end in Skyfire to await *their* turn). We went out and helped her kill Ragefire, and then returned to our business in PoG. <br>
We actually left the zone, totally abandoned, and then came back to continue. I still don't think that this *should* have costed us our turn on Tunare, and it didn't.<br>
